# GEMINI_API_KEY is server-only (Worker). Do not put it in the frontend bundle.
#
# Local dev (optional — same name as Cloudflare):
#   Project root `.dev.vars` (gitignored) — see `.dev.vars.example`
#   Or `GEMINI_API_KEY` in `.env.local` (gitignored)
#
# Production (required for https://your-domain/... — e.g. maxmvs.com):
#   The secret must exist on the SAME Worker that serves the site (name in wrangler.jsonc, e.g. macrocounter-ai).
#   Git-connected Workers: do NOT put GEMINI_API_KEY only under Build (next to “Build command”).
#   Those are build-time variables — they are not passed to env at request time, so the Worker still sees
#   Missing GEMINI_API_KEY. Add the key under Worker Settings → Variables and secrets (runtime), as a Secret.
#   1) Cloudflare Dashboard → Workers & Pages → your project → Settings → Variables and Secrets (Worker / Production)
#   2) Add variable name exactly: GEMINI_API_KEY → type Secret (encrypted) → paste your Google AI key → Save
#   Or CLI (logged into the same account): npx wrangler secret put GEMINI_API_KEY
#   If you use a custom domain, the secret still lives on this Worker — not on DNS-only records.
#   `npm run deploy` strips `.dev.vars` from dist; it does NOT set production secrets.
#
# Browser console: net::ERR_BLOCKED_BY_CLIENT is usually an ad-blocker/privacy extension blocking a URL —
# not an app bug. Try disabling extensions for your site or allowlisting it.

# APP_URL: The URL where this applet is hosted.
# AI Studio automatically injects this at runtime with the Cloud Run service URL.
# Used for self-referential links, OAuth callbacks, and API endpoints.
APP_URL="MY_APP_URL"
